#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-np12"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. HTML: </p><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:0.3"
msgid "Nissaggiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on relinquishment"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:0.4"
msgid "Kosiyavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Relinquishment"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:0.5"
msgid "12. Suddhakāḷakasikkhāpada"
msgstr "12. The training rule on entirely black"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-cs-bu-np12.1, pts-vp-en2.74, ms1V_2109
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Vesālī in the hall with the peaked roof in the Great Wood."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū suddhakāḷakānaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ santhataṃ kārāpenti."
msgstr "At that time the monks from the group of six were getting blankets made entirely of black wool."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:1.3"
msgid "Manussā vihāracārikaṃ āhiṇḍantā passitvā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People who were walking about the dwellings grumbled and complained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:1.4"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā suddhakāḷakānaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ santhataṃ kārāpessanti, seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti."
msgstr "“How can the Sakyan ascetics get blankets made entirely of black wool, just like lay people who indulge in sensual pleasures?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms1V_2110
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:1.5"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:1.6"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:1.7"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:1.8"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū suddhakāḷakānaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ santhataṃ kārāpessantī”ti."
msgstr "“How can the monks from the group of six get blankets made entirely of black wool?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3, ms1V_2111
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:1.9"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū chabbaggiye bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:1.10"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, suddhakāḷakānaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ santhataṃ kārāpethā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:1.11"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:1.12"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:1.13"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, suddhakāḷakānaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ santhataṃ kārāpessatha."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you get blankets made entirely of black wool?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:1.14"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:1.15"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:1.15a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc4, ms1V_2112
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:1.16"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu suddhakāḷakānaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ santhataṃ kārāpeyya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk gets a blanket made entirely of black wool, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc5, pts-cs-bu-np12.2, pts-vp-en2.75, ms1V_2113
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever … "

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc6, ms1V_2114
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.6"
msgid "Kāḷakaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Black:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.7"
msgid "dve kāḷakāni—"
msgstr "there are two kinds of black:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.8"
msgid "jātiyā kāḷakaṃ vā rajanakāḷakaṃ vā."
msgstr "natural black and dyed black."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc7, ms1V_2115
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.9"
msgid "Santhataṃ nāma"
msgstr "A blanket:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.10"
msgid "santharitvā kataṃ hoti avāyimaṃ."
msgstr "it is made by spreading out, not by weaving."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, pts-vp-pli3.226, ms1V_2116
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.11"
msgid "Kārāpeyyāti"
msgstr "Gets made:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.12"
msgid "karoti vā kārāpeti vā, payoge dukkaṭaṃ."
msgstr "for the act of making the blanket, or getting it made, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.13"
msgid "Paṭilābhena nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "When he gets the blanket, it becomes subject to relinquishment."

#. HTML: </span></p><hr><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.14"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr "The blanket should be relinquished to an Order, a group, or an individual."

#. HTML: <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.15"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ …"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way. …"

#. HTML: <span class="pe"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.16"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "To be expanded as in [Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17](pli-tv-bu-vb-np1#13), with appropriate substitutions. "

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.17"
msgid "“idaṃ me, bhante, suddhakāḷakānaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ santhataṃ kārāpitaṃ nissaggiyaṃ."
msgstr "‘Venerables, this blanket which I got made entirely of black wool is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.18"
msgid "Imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’ …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.19"
msgid "dadeyyāti … pe …"
msgstr "the Order should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.20"
msgid "dadeyyunti … pe …"
msgstr "you should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.21"
msgid "āyasmato dammīti."
msgstr "‘I give this blanket back to you.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.21a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc9, ms1V_2117
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.22"
msgid "Attanā vippakataṃ attanā pariyosāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If he finishes what he began himself, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.23"
msgid "Attanā vippakataṃ parehi pariyosāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If he gets others to finish what he began himself, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.24"
msgid "Parehi vippakataṃ attanā pariyosāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If he finishes himself what was begun by others, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.25"
msgid "Parehi vippakataṃ parehi pariyosāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If he gets others to finish what was begun by others, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10, ms1V_2118
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.26"
msgid "Aññassatthāya karoti vā kārāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he makes one, or gets one made, for someone else, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.27"
msgid "Aññena kataṃ paṭilabhitvā paribhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he obtains one that was made by someone else and then uses it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.27a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc11, ms1V_2119
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.28"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.29"
msgid "vitānaṃ vā bhūmattharaṇaṃ vā sāṇipākāraṃ vā bhisiṃ vā bibbohanaṃ vā karoti,"
msgstr "if he makes a canopy, a floor cover, a screen-wall, a mattress, or a pillow;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.30"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.31"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc12, ms1V_2120
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np12:2.32"
msgid "Suddhakāḷakasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ."
msgstr "The second rule, the training rule on entirely black, is finished."
